My co-worker Belinda Liu turned to me and said, &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t like these tests at all; they&rsquo;re hard to follow, and I&rsquo;m not sure what they&rsquo;re testing.&rdquo;
I looked at the tests that I had spent much of yesterday afternoon working on. She was right: they were hard to follow (even for me, who had written some of them!).
How had we gotten here? Our code was straightforward, but our tests were byzantine (excessively complicated).
